1
00:00:50,583 --> 00:00:52,118
Norigae Vote.

2
00:00:53,019 --> 00:00:56,756
(A box of norigae
bearing the 10 contestants' names)

3
00:00:56,756 --> 00:01:00,560
Put a norigae in the box
of one person you're interested in...

4
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:02,295
to show how you feel.

5
00:01:02,295 --> 00:01:05,798
Who voted for whom will remain a secret.

6
00:01:06,132 --> 00:01:10,103
(A moment to reflect
on the day and their feelings)

7
00:01:10,303 --> 00:01:14,240
(All 10 contestants
have completed their votes.)

8
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:17,343
I think the votes may be
somewhat concentrated.

9
00:01:17,343 --> 00:01:18,211
Right.

10
00:01:18,211 --> 00:01:19,646
When everyone is around...

11
00:01:19,646 --> 00:01:21,147
Right, they kept doing it
in front of everyone.

12
00:01:21,147 --> 00:01:23,983
It feels a little awkward,
but there, they can just...

13
00:01:23,983 --> 00:01:25,351
Be honest.

14
00:01:25,652 --> 00:01:26,753
(Checking the voting results
with the mothers)

15
00:01:26,753 --> 00:01:29,188
We come out one by one to vote.

16
00:01:29,188 --> 00:01:31,391
It's so cruel to see that
with their mothers.

17
00:01:31,391 --> 00:01:33,459
Seeing it with your mom is the cruel part.

18
00:01:36,195 --> 00:01:40,366
(Lee In Kwon and his mother
check his box.)

19
00:01:42,201 --> 00:01:44,604
Stay humble.

20
00:01:46,205 --> 00:01:47,941
- No.
- No?

21
00:01:47,941 --> 00:01:49,576
- It feels light.
- Does it?

22
00:01:55,081 --> 00:01:57,417
- There is one.
- One.

23
00:01:57,417 --> 00:01:58,251
What a relief.

24
00:01:58,251 --> 00:01:59,285
(Norigae Vote, Lee In Kwon, 1 vote)

25
00:02:02,222 --> 00:02:04,290
How grateful.

26
00:02:06,826 --> 00:02:08,461
I can't believe I'm this happy.

27
00:02:08,461 --> 00:02:10,463
I'm so thankful. Who is it?

28
00:02:10,463 --> 00:02:11,297
We don't know that.

29
00:02:11,297 --> 00:02:12,632
You have to return the favor.

30
00:02:13,166 --> 00:02:16,536
Maybe Do Yoon put one in.

31
00:02:16,769 --> 00:02:19,472
I thought, "I hope it was Do Yoon."

32
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:22,175
(Who gave him the pink norigae?)

33
00:02:22,175 --> 00:02:24,210
There's a very high chance it was Do Yoon.

34
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:26,679
- Yes, it is.
- It's Do Yoon.

35
00:02:26,679 --> 00:02:29,849
I gave my norigae to Ahn Do Yoon.

36
00:02:29,849 --> 00:02:33,886
I think Do Yoon may feel the same way,

37
00:02:33,886 --> 00:02:37,257
that she may have given one to me too.

38
00:02:37,590 --> 00:02:39,626
They voted for each other.

39
00:02:39,926 --> 00:02:41,794
(Kang Shin Woo and his mother
check his box.)

40
00:02:41,794 --> 00:02:42,795
"Kang Shin Woo."

41
00:02:43,596 --> 00:02:44,430
Would you close your eyes?

42
00:02:45,398 --> 00:02:46,299
Should I open it?

43
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:50,236
If I get zero again,

44
00:02:50,236 --> 00:02:52,939
my mother might actually cry.

45
00:02:52,939 --> 00:02:54,474
I hope Da Hye put hers in.

46
00:02:55,642 --> 00:02:56,643
Close your eyes.

47
00:02:57,343 --> 00:02:59,445
Drumroll. What now?

48
00:02:59,445 --> 00:03:01,080
Will there be one?

49
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:03,716
(Norigae Vote, Kang Shin Woo, 1 vote)

50
00:03:03,716 --> 00:03:04,851
What a relief.

51
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:06,052
One.

52
00:03:06,052 --> 00:03:07,787
They had to give him one there.

53
00:03:07,787 --> 00:03:10,957
Because if he got zero there too,
his mother would really...

54
00:03:10,957 --> 00:03:12,025
Right.

55
00:03:12,025 --> 00:03:14,761
- I was worried she'd be heartbroken.
- Right.

56
00:03:15,528 --> 00:03:16,696
Yes!

57
00:03:18,631 --> 00:03:20,199
You're taking it?

58
00:03:20,199 --> 00:03:21,100
Yes.

59
00:03:23,202 --> 00:03:25,705
He's no longer at zero.

60
00:03:26,673 --> 00:03:28,775
I wondered, "Who could it be?"

61
00:03:29,442 --> 00:03:31,477
Since the first-impression picks,

62
00:03:31,811 --> 00:03:33,913
Da Hye was the only one
I had feelings for.

63
00:03:33,913 --> 00:03:36,482
I decided I should choose Da Hye,
so I did.

64
00:03:37,283 --> 00:03:39,919
Right. A one-woman man suits him.

65
00:03:39,919 --> 00:03:43,923
Da Hye had pretty pale lavender nails,

66
00:03:44,324 --> 00:03:47,460
and there was
a pale lavender norigae in there,

67
00:03:47,460 --> 00:03:50,263
so I thought it might be her way
of signaling that it was hers.

68
00:03:50,263 --> 00:03:51,764
(Could Da Hye have left
a pale lavender hint?)

69
00:03:53,866 --> 00:03:56,102
I gave mine to Shin Woo.

70
00:03:56,102 --> 00:03:59,239
Da Hye gave hers to Shin Woo too.

71
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:04,043
Beneath his gentle-looking exterior,

72
00:04:04,043 --> 00:04:07,480
there was a hidden sharpness...

73
00:04:08,214 --> 00:04:10,750
that made me want to know more about him.

74
00:04:11,184 --> 00:04:14,787
(Their feelings connected
on the first night.)

75
00:04:15,154 --> 00:04:17,490
(Kim Dong Young and his mother
check his box.)

76
00:04:17,490 --> 00:04:18,524
Dong Young.

77
00:04:18,524 --> 00:04:20,126
It's a critical moment for him.

78
00:04:20,126 --> 00:04:21,995
There might not be a single vote in there.

79
00:04:22,495 --> 00:04:24,130
- Drumroll.
- Drumroll.

80
00:04:25,064 --> 00:04:25,899
Who should open it?

81
00:04:25,899 --> 00:04:26,799
You open it, Mom.

82
00:04:30,637 --> 00:04:31,504
(Norigae Vote, Kim Dong Young, 0 votes)

83
00:04:31,504 --> 00:04:33,539
- See? I knew it.
- My goodness.

84
00:04:35,642 --> 00:04:37,176
There's nothing.

85
00:04:38,678 --> 00:04:42,582
But he got a vote from Ha Yoon
in the first-impression picks.

86
00:04:43,683 --> 00:04:45,285
- Because...
- Maybe because he didn't go after her.

87
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:47,720
he didn't go after her.

88
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:49,155
Karma.

89
00:04:50,590 --> 00:04:51,758
What do we do?

90
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:54,260
What now?

91
00:04:54,260 --> 00:04:55,194
Well...

92
00:04:57,964 --> 00:04:58,965
Cheer up. You can do it.

93
00:04:58,965 --> 00:04:59,866
I can do it.

94
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:03,002
I thought he'd get at least one vote.

95
00:05:03,002 --> 00:05:05,338
But he got none,
and that made me a little sad.

96
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:10,910
My mother looked so clearly disappointed,

97
00:05:12,445 --> 00:05:15,682
so I thought
I should pull myself together.

98
00:05:15,682 --> 00:05:16,883
That's what I thought.

99
00:05:17,917 --> 00:05:20,753
It's because you didn't pick Ha Yoon.

100
00:05:20,753 --> 00:05:22,255
That's not it.

101
00:05:22,255 --> 00:05:23,156
Still...

102
00:05:25,191 --> 00:05:26,092
It's okay.

103
00:05:26,092 --> 00:05:27,594
But I think you were fine.

104
00:05:28,428 --> 00:05:30,797
(Dong Young's feelings)

105
00:05:30,797 --> 00:05:35,201
I really wanted
to get to know Ha Yoon better.

106
00:05:35,735 --> 00:05:38,271
Not just because I felt sorry,

107
00:05:38,271 --> 00:05:39,606
but after talking to her,

108
00:05:39,606 --> 00:05:41,908
I wanted to get to know her even better.

109
00:05:41,908 --> 00:05:43,776
That's why I chose her.

110
00:05:46,246 --> 00:05:49,816
(The man with two first-impression votes,
Kwon Ye Chan, enters.)

111
00:05:50,683 --> 00:05:52,785
- The popular guy, Ye Chan.
- Ye Chan.

112
00:05:55,421 --> 00:05:58,358
(He opens the box without hesitation.)

113
00:05:59,325 --> 00:06:00,326
About two...

114
00:06:00,326 --> 00:06:03,263
(Norigae Vote, Kwon Ye Chan, 2 votes)

115
00:06:03,263 --> 00:06:04,564
You were right. Two.

116
00:06:04,564 --> 00:06:06,266
(Kwon Ye Chan gets 2 votes,
just as Yo Han predicted.)

117
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:11,404
(He gets 2 votes again
after the first-impression picks.)

118
00:06:15,508 --> 00:06:16,476
I think...

119
00:06:17,877 --> 00:06:20,413
I mean, if I were Da Hye,

120
00:06:21,581 --> 00:06:24,450
since I didn't step out when the men made
their first-impression picks...

121
00:06:25,585 --> 00:06:27,520
That's what I think.

122
00:06:28,588 --> 00:06:30,857
(Then who did Jeong Yoon choose?)

123
00:06:31,991 --> 00:06:34,394
Jeong Yoon chose Ye Chan.

124
00:06:34,394 --> 00:06:35,295
Yes.

125
00:06:35,295 --> 00:06:39,365
(Who gave the other vote?)

126
00:06:39,365 --> 00:06:40,300
Who is it?

127
00:06:41,834 --> 00:06:42,902
(It was Yang Ha Yoon.)

128
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:43,736
Ha Yoon.

129
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:46,773
I gave Ye Chan my norigae.

130
00:06:46,773 --> 00:06:48,641
(Norigae Vote,
Yang Ha Yoon voted for Kwon Ye Chan.)

131
00:06:49,542 --> 00:06:51,444
Right before that,

132
00:06:51,444 --> 00:06:53,746
he had lent me his cardigan.

133
00:06:53,913 --> 00:06:56,583
(Before the interest vote)

134
00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:58,084
Aren't you cold? Are you okay?

135
00:06:58,084 --> 00:06:59,686
You must be cold, Ha Yoon.

136
00:06:59,686 --> 00:07:01,654
No, I'm fine. Let's go.

137
00:07:02,155 --> 00:07:03,556
- Put this on.
- I'm fine.

138
00:07:03,556 --> 00:07:05,491
I'm wearing something thick anyway.

139
00:07:05,491 --> 00:07:06,492
Thank you.

140
00:07:06,492 --> 00:07:08,328
(Ye Chan readily lends
Ha Yoon his cardigan.)

141
00:07:08,328 --> 00:07:09,429
Really?

142
00:07:09,762 --> 00:07:13,166
A small kindness toward
a woman with zero votes...

143
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:15,501
can lead to major interest.

144
00:07:15,501 --> 00:07:16,936
So be careful, everyone.

145
00:07:18,871 --> 00:07:20,173
I'm telling all of you to watch out.

146
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:23,109
Moon Seong Mo.

147
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:26,379
There has to be one in there, right?

148
00:07:30,350 --> 00:07:31,317
Open it.

149
00:07:34,721 --> 00:07:35,622
Look.

150
00:07:35,622 --> 00:07:36,556
What is it?

151
00:07:39,359 --> 00:07:40,560
(Norigae Vote, Moon Seong Mo, 1 vote)

152
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:41,494
One vote.

153
00:07:42,128 --> 00:07:43,196
Kang Hyeon?

154
00:07:43,196 --> 00:07:44,063
Is that it?

155
00:07:44,063 --> 00:07:46,799
You don't have to tell us who put it.

156
00:07:50,703 --> 00:07:51,771
Kang Hyeon.

157
00:07:51,771 --> 00:07:53,973
(Norigae Vote,
Lee Kang Hyeon voted for Moon Seong Mo.)

158
00:07:54,774 --> 00:07:56,476
What do I do?

159
00:07:56,476 --> 00:07:57,343
Why?

160
00:07:57,343 --> 00:07:58,778
It gives me a lot to think about.

161
00:07:58,778 --> 00:07:59,979
It does?

162
00:08:00,613 --> 00:08:02,415
I think...

163
00:08:02,415 --> 00:08:04,050
she voted for me.

164
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:06,819
But I think he gave his to someone else.

165
00:08:08,021 --> 00:08:10,056
(Who did Seong Mo choose?)

166
00:08:10,056 --> 00:08:11,124
You open it, Mom.

167
00:08:11,124 --> 00:08:12,091
What?

168
00:08:12,091 --> 00:08:13,226
You open it, Mom.

169
00:08:13,226 --> 00:08:14,327
Wait.

170
00:08:17,263 --> 00:08:18,565
- Open it.
- What do we do?

171
00:08:20,099 --> 00:08:21,034
Why?

172
00:08:22,468 --> 00:08:24,170
Her face doesn't look good.

173
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:26,406
- There's nothing. No.
- There's nothing.

174
00:08:27,407 --> 00:08:34,380
(Norigae Vote, Lee Kang Hyeon, 0 votes)

175
00:08:35,481 --> 00:08:36,382
Let's go.

176
00:08:38,251 --> 00:08:40,787
Kang Hyeon got zero votes. What do we do?

177
00:08:40,787 --> 00:08:42,088
I told you.

178
00:08:42,088 --> 00:08:44,290
I was a little worried.

179
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:45,458
What do we do?

180
00:08:45,458 --> 00:08:46,926
Seong Mo also said...

181
00:08:46,926 --> 00:08:49,796
that he finds women who come on
too strong overwhelming.

182
00:08:51,397 --> 00:08:53,533
- Mom, I'm okay.
- Okay.

183
00:08:54,334 --> 00:08:55,635
Okay.

184
00:08:58,037 --> 00:08:59,339
- Are you okay, Mom?
- Yes.

185
00:08:59,339 --> 00:09:00,707
I'm really okay.

186
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:01,574
Okay.

187
00:09:03,209 --> 00:09:05,278
I thought there'd be at least one,

188
00:09:05,278 --> 00:09:06,980
but there wasn't.

189
00:09:07,814 --> 00:09:09,449
So I felt so bad for her.

190
00:09:09,449 --> 00:09:11,551
Kang Hyeon must be disappointed.

191
00:09:13,353 --> 00:09:15,188
Maybe Kang Hyeon was a little too much.

192
00:09:15,188 --> 00:09:16,823
Well...

193
00:09:16,823 --> 00:09:18,391
Well...

194
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:19,459
Ma'am.

195
00:09:19,826 --> 00:09:21,160
"A little too much."

196
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:22,295
(The mother's brutally honest take)

197
00:09:22,295 --> 00:09:23,363
Goodness.

198
00:09:24,497 --> 00:09:25,999
Kang Hyeon is a little...

199
00:09:25,999 --> 00:09:27,500
too much when she gets excited.

200
00:09:28,101 --> 00:09:31,504
She doesn't hold back or read the room.

201
00:09:31,504 --> 00:09:32,672
I think...

202
00:09:32,672 --> 00:09:34,140
when everyone was busy cooking
in the kitchen and all,

203
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:36,042
she was a little too much.

204
00:09:39,012 --> 00:09:41,848
She really knows her daughter best.

205
00:09:41,848 --> 00:09:45,218
- She does.
- She knows her daughter best.

206
00:09:45,218 --> 00:09:46,586
She's being completely honest.

207
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,655
She sure speaks plainly.

208
00:09:48,922 --> 00:09:50,356
(Choi Jeong Yoon and her mother
check her box.)

209
00:09:50,356 --> 00:09:51,291
Okay.

210
00:09:57,764 --> 00:09:58,665
What a relief.

211
00:09:59,065 --> 00:10:00,433
(Norigae Vote, Choi Jeong Yoon, 2 votes)

212
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:02,835
Jeong Yoon got two votes.

213
00:10:05,204 --> 00:10:06,272
She's so happy.

214
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:09,042
What a relief.

215
00:10:09,776 --> 00:10:11,978
I voted for Jeong Yoon.

216
00:10:15,415 --> 00:10:20,653
(Norigae Vote,
Kwon Ye Chan voted for Choi Jeong Yoon.)

217
00:10:21,454 --> 00:10:23,323
(And one more person
voted for Jeong Yoon.)

218
00:10:23,323 --> 00:10:24,824
Who gave the other one?

219
00:10:24,824 --> 00:10:26,926
- This person.
- Seong Mo.

220
00:10:28,962 --> 00:10:31,664
I wanted to get to know Jeong Yoon too,

221
00:10:31,898 --> 00:10:34,000
so I wanted to give it another shot.

222
00:10:36,035 --> 00:10:37,370
I'm so relieved.

223
00:10:37,904 --> 00:10:39,005
I should do better.

224
00:10:39,973 --> 00:10:40,974
Good luck.

225
00:10:40,974 --> 00:10:41,874
Okay.

226
00:10:42,842 --> 00:10:45,645
(After the interest vote)

227
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:46,946
Do you think it's over with Kang Hyeon?

228
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:48,681
No?

229
00:10:49,415 --> 00:10:51,251
I just like her as a person.

230
00:10:51,251 --> 00:10:53,519
But this is what we talked about earlier.

231
00:10:54,354 --> 00:10:55,722
(Before the interest vote)

232
00:10:55,722 --> 00:10:58,124
What if your parents strongly oppose it?

233
00:10:58,124 --> 00:10:59,859
- My parents?
- What would you do?

234
00:10:59,859 --> 00:11:01,160
If they opposed it,

235
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:04,931
I don't think I could go through
with the marriage.

236
00:11:04,931 --> 00:11:06,532
I see.

237
00:11:06,532 --> 00:11:08,601
That's unexpected, Kang Hyeon.

238
00:11:09,302 --> 00:11:11,237
What if you love them so much? Then what?

239
00:11:12,405 --> 00:11:13,907
Even if I loved them very much,

240
00:11:13,907 --> 00:11:17,010
I'd think there must be a reason
if they object.

241
00:11:18,444 --> 00:11:22,615
I don't think I can ignore
the wisdom that comes with age.

242
00:11:22,615 --> 00:11:25,885
If her mom objects, she does too?

243
00:11:25,885 --> 00:11:27,954
That kind of...

244
00:11:27,954 --> 00:11:29,556
makes her seem not fully independent.

245
00:11:30,590 --> 00:11:32,191
When a problem came up,

246
00:11:32,191 --> 00:11:35,895
I got the sense
she'd follow her parents' wishes.

247
00:11:35,895 --> 00:11:38,431
That lowered my interest quite a bit.

248
00:11:39,098 --> 00:11:41,467
She could come across as a mama's girl.

249
00:11:42,035 --> 00:11:44,170
But Jeong Yoon, on the other hand...

250
00:11:44,170 --> 00:11:45,271
I'll have to persuade them.

251
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:48,675
Persuade them.

252
00:11:48,675 --> 00:11:50,009
What if you can't?

253
00:11:50,243 --> 00:11:51,578
I'll keep trying until I can.

254
00:11:53,780 --> 00:11:57,283
That made me like Jeong Yoon more.

255
00:11:58,818 --> 00:12:00,420
- What do I do?
- It's okay.

256
00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:02,188
(Meanwhile,
Kang Hyeon goes from 1 vote to 0.)

257
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:07,260
How do you date, Mom?

258
00:12:10,330 --> 00:12:11,631
You're supposed to feel butterflies.

259
00:12:12,865 --> 00:12:14,133
Aren't you supposed to feel butterflies?

260
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:15,602
But you never felt butterflies for Dad.

261
00:12:15,602 --> 00:12:16,769
No, I don't have that.

262
00:12:18,371 --> 00:12:19,372
"I don't have that."

263
00:12:19,372 --> 00:12:21,007
(As the zero-vote woman learns
what real-life dating is like,)

264
00:12:21,541 --> 00:12:23,610
(Ye Chan and his mother relax
with his two votes.)

265
00:12:23,610 --> 00:12:25,144
That is his mother,

266
00:12:25,144 --> 00:12:27,280
but from behind, I keep getting startled.

267
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:28,748
I get mixed up.

268
00:12:29,415 --> 00:12:30,917
Just looking at her like this...

269
00:12:30,917 --> 00:12:32,485
From behind...

270
00:12:33,319 --> 00:12:36,656
Be more assertive, okay?

271
00:12:36,656 --> 00:12:38,858
You don't win at relationships
by being aggressive.

272
00:12:39,459 --> 00:12:40,326
Really?

273
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:42,362
Then what should you do?

274
00:12:42,362 --> 00:12:43,997
Just go with the flow.

275
00:12:43,997 --> 00:12:45,198
Really?

276
00:12:45,198 --> 00:12:46,499
I don't think that applies here.

277
00:12:46,499 --> 00:12:47,533
No.

278
00:12:48,268 --> 00:12:50,069
Being aggressive can be overwhelming.

279
00:12:50,069 --> 00:12:50,970
Really?

280
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:52,405
That's not wrong.

281
00:12:52,405 --> 00:12:53,373
- Right.
- Yes.

282
00:12:55,008 --> 00:12:55,708
(Knock, knock)

283
00:12:55,708 --> 00:12:56,910
Yes?

284
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:59,379
(Someone visits Ye Chan's room?)

285
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:01,581
- Hello.
- Hello.

286
00:13:01,581 --> 00:13:03,483
I came to return your cardigan.

287
00:13:03,483 --> 00:13:04,317
Thanks.

288
00:13:04,317 --> 00:13:05,285
(Ha Yoon returns
the cardigan Ye Chan lent her.)

289
00:13:05,285 --> 00:13:07,954
- Another opportunity.
- Exactly.

290
00:13:07,954 --> 00:13:10,690
I also came because I wanted to talk.

291
00:13:10,690 --> 00:13:12,625
- Let's go, then.
- No, but...

292
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:14,394
- I'm not tired at all.
- But you must be tired.

293
00:13:14,394 --> 00:13:15,862
No, I'm not tired at all.

294
00:13:17,096 --> 00:13:18,264
But aren't you cold?

295
00:13:18,264 --> 00:13:19,999
I'm wearing a really warm coat.

296
00:13:19,999 --> 00:13:22,368
- Then let's take a walk.
- You got cold because of me, didn't you?

297
00:13:23,570 --> 00:13:25,371
We haven't had a chance to talk.

298
00:13:25,972 --> 00:13:27,774
I talked briefly with the others,

299
00:13:27,774 --> 00:13:29,943
or talked with their parents.

300
00:13:31,377 --> 00:13:33,713
I have a feeling
you work in a similar field to mine...

301
00:13:34,747 --> 00:13:35,582
somehow.

302
00:13:35,582 --> 00:13:36,482
Wait a second.

303
00:13:38,384 --> 00:13:40,320
Though I don't know what it is.

304
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,220
But you might be right.

305
00:13:41,220 --> 00:13:42,188
Really?

306
00:13:43,323 --> 00:13:45,258
Because you don't get
a hunch like that easily.

307
00:13:45,792 --> 00:13:46,859
I could be wrong.

308
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:49,062
I could be wrong after saying all this.

309
00:13:50,463 --> 00:13:51,431
Ha Yoon.

310
00:13:51,431 --> 00:13:54,000
- Dong Young is late.
- Dong Young.

311
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:54,934
Are you there?

312
00:13:57,270 --> 00:13:58,805
(Ha Yoon's mother appears.)

313
00:13:59,539 --> 00:14:00,740
(Ma'am)

314
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:01,774
Hello.

315
00:14:01,774 --> 00:14:03,209
Ha Yoon is not...

316
00:14:03,710 --> 00:14:05,812
- Okay, I'll come back later.
- Okay.

317
00:14:05,812 --> 00:14:07,513
(Dong Young meets only Ha Yoon's mother.)

318
00:14:08,047 --> 00:14:10,250
No.

319
00:14:10,250 --> 00:14:11,751
His face...

320
00:14:11,751 --> 00:14:16,122
You can already see
the disappointment wash over his face.

321
00:14:18,491 --> 00:14:19,659
You keep missing your chances.

322
00:14:19,659 --> 00:14:20,493
Yeah.

323
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:23,997
Why are you doing that?

324
00:14:25,164 --> 00:14:30,737
I think the first-impression pick
affected Ha Yoon.

325
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:34,440
And that probably...

326
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:38,278
may have hurt her,
even if she doesn't show it.

327
00:14:39,512 --> 00:14:41,047
Honestly, right now,

328
00:14:41,047 --> 00:14:43,983
I'm not drawn to Jeong Yoon right now.

329
00:14:43,983 --> 00:14:46,019
Right, I like Ha Yoon better too.

330
00:14:46,953 --> 00:14:50,323
After talking to her, she seemed
to have such a nice personality.

331
00:14:50,323 --> 00:14:51,157
Shall we look for it?

332
00:14:51,157 --> 00:14:52,191
Carrying water.

333
00:14:52,191 --> 00:14:53,793
(Ha Yoon's bubbly charm)

334
00:14:53,793 --> 00:14:55,128
(Chuckling)

335
00:14:55,128 --> 00:14:56,362
He thought she was adorable just then.

336
00:14:56,362 --> 00:14:57,797
That was definitely what he thought.

337
00:14:57,797 --> 00:14:58,998
This is bad.

338
00:14:59,699 --> 00:15:02,769
I feel like you let the best one get away.

339
00:15:02,769 --> 00:15:03,937
- From the start?
- Yes.

340
00:15:05,238 --> 00:15:06,406
Let's focus on one person now.

341
00:15:07,006 --> 00:15:09,742
- You shouldn't focus on just one.
- Mom says to focus on just one.

342
00:15:09,742 --> 00:15:11,911
I think there's still a slight chance,

343
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:14,948
because Dong Young seems like
he'll keep going straight for her.

344
00:15:14,948 --> 00:15:18,117
So maybe she'll accept
his sincerity someday.

345
00:15:18,651 --> 00:15:21,821
The only man who gave her zero votes?

346
00:15:21,821 --> 00:15:24,290
I think...

347
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:26,492
he should wait outside her door,
and when she comes in,

348
00:15:27,493 --> 00:15:28,761
get on his knees.

349
00:15:29,896 --> 00:15:31,798
He has to get on his knees?

350
00:15:31,798 --> 00:15:35,101
"Earlier, I really wasn't myself."

351
00:15:35,101 --> 00:15:37,637
"I was out of my mind.
That wasn't the real me."

352
00:15:37,637 --> 00:15:40,707
Otherwise, I think it'll be hard.

353
00:15:42,675 --> 00:15:43,243
(Knock, knock)

354
00:15:43,243 --> 00:15:44,077
Yes?

355
00:15:45,144 --> 00:15:46,479
The door's open.

356
00:15:46,479 --> 00:15:48,081
(Someone knocks on In Kwon's door?)

357
00:15:48,081 --> 00:15:50,083
In Kwon, can we talk?

358
00:15:50,083 --> 00:15:51,417
Of course.

359
00:15:52,619 --> 00:15:54,721
(Do Yoon comes to see In Kwon.)

360
00:15:54,721 --> 00:15:56,189
Over there...

361
00:15:56,189 --> 00:15:57,557
Things are going very smoothly.

362
00:15:58,424 --> 00:15:59,592
It was Do Yoon.

363
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:02,228
She came to see me a second time.

364
00:16:02,228 --> 00:16:04,864
Once at the first-impression picks
and once at the end of the day.

365
00:16:06,866 --> 00:16:08,568
What's your favorite color?

366
00:16:08,568 --> 00:16:09,769
- Color?
- Yes.

367
00:16:09,769 --> 00:16:11,638
Pink.

368
00:16:11,638 --> 00:16:12,672
Pink?

369
00:16:17,744 --> 00:16:19,913
I didn't know a book café was here.

370
00:16:20,947 --> 00:16:23,316
- Thank you.
- Don't mention it.

371
00:16:23,316 --> 00:16:24,450
Thank you.

372
00:16:24,450 --> 00:16:25,551
(In Kwon gets Do Yoon some water first.)

373
00:16:29,122 --> 00:16:30,823
You checked the norigae vote, right?

374
00:16:30,823 --> 00:16:31,658
Yes.

375
00:16:31,658 --> 00:16:32,992
You must have gotten a lot.

376
00:16:34,193 --> 00:16:35,795
- No.
- I don't know either.

377
00:16:36,596 --> 00:16:37,931
But we...

378
00:16:39,299 --> 00:16:40,433
When I opened it,

379
00:16:42,769 --> 00:16:44,103
there was a pink norigae.

380
00:16:44,103 --> 00:16:45,104
Really?

381
00:16:46,739 --> 00:16:47,607
Right.

382
00:16:47,607 --> 00:16:50,743
So that's why he asked her favorite color.

383
00:16:50,743 --> 00:16:53,246
Seriously?

384
00:16:55,214 --> 00:16:58,818
At the first-impression picks,

385
00:16:58,818 --> 00:17:01,688
I thought maybe you chose me...

386
00:17:01,688 --> 00:17:04,023
just because we were sitting close.

387
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:07,327
I thought that would be the main reason.

388
00:17:07,327 --> 00:17:09,095
But after that,

389
00:17:09,095 --> 00:17:12,098
when we got to the lodging
and you opened the window...

390
00:17:12,565 --> 00:17:14,000
and looked outside...

391
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,535
I was so happy to see you...

392
00:17:15,535 --> 00:17:16,536
when I spotted you.

393
00:17:17,537 --> 00:17:19,005
(She hears In Kwon's voice outside.)

394
00:17:19,005 --> 00:17:20,573
(Turn)

395
00:17:21,241 --> 00:17:23,476
(Peek)

396
00:17:24,344 --> 00:17:25,011
(Hi)

397
00:17:25,011 --> 00:17:26,446
Which room are you in?

398
00:17:26,446 --> 00:17:27,347
Room One.

399
00:17:27,347 --> 00:17:29,682
(The two had greeted each other
through the window.)

400
00:17:30,016 --> 00:17:31,618
- I was really happy to see you.
- Really?

401
00:17:34,254 --> 00:17:36,756
When I see the two of them together,

402
00:17:36,756 --> 00:17:37,657
they give off such a good vibe.

403
00:17:37,657 --> 00:17:39,158
They have really similar vibes.

404
00:17:39,158 --> 00:17:40,693
They look great together.

405
00:17:40,693 --> 00:17:41,661
Yes, they do.

406
00:17:43,129 --> 00:17:45,331
Tomorrow and after that,

407
00:17:45,331 --> 00:17:48,334
there will probably be
plenty of chances...

408
00:17:49,068 --> 00:17:51,838
to talk with the others too.

409
00:17:57,477 --> 00:17:58,611
After that,

410
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:03,149
- talk to me too.
- Of course.

411
00:18:03,149 --> 00:18:04,083
Okay.

412
00:18:05,018 --> 00:18:05,919
Okay.

413
00:18:06,986 --> 00:18:10,123
After talking more,

414
00:18:10,123 --> 00:18:11,457
my interest in her grew.

415
00:18:13,626 --> 00:18:15,428
She's someone...

416
00:18:15,428 --> 00:18:18,765
I want to get to know
much better going forward.

417
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:22,535
Why didn't you go see Seong Mo?

418
00:18:22,535 --> 00:18:24,170
Seong Mo didn't choose me.

419
00:18:24,170 --> 00:18:25,538
- Really?
- Yes.

420
00:18:26,139 --> 00:18:27,073
Who did he choose?

421
00:18:27,073 --> 00:18:30,610
So I didn't get any votes.

422
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:34,013
That makes it hard for me
to just walk up to him.

423
00:18:34,714 --> 00:18:36,015
Is there anyone you're curious about?

424
00:18:36,015 --> 00:18:37,517
Anyone you want to talk to more?

425
00:18:37,517 --> 00:18:38,985
There's only Ye Chan for me.

426
00:18:38,985 --> 00:18:39,953
Go for it.

427
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:43,890
(Ye Chan happens to be wandering by.)

428
00:18:44,424 --> 00:18:45,692
Just walk around naturally.

429
00:18:48,461 --> 00:18:49,362
Hello.

430
00:18:50,463 --> 00:18:51,631
Everyone's pairing up.

431
00:18:52,498 --> 00:18:53,666
Were you two walking around here together?

432
00:18:53,666 --> 00:18:55,235
That's right.

433
00:18:55,235 --> 00:18:56,703
- Shall we walk together?
- Shall we?

434
00:18:56,703 --> 00:18:58,705
- Which way should we go? That way?
- Sounds good.

435
00:18:59,606 --> 00:19:01,241
Then I'll head inside.

436
00:19:01,241 --> 00:19:02,175
See you tomorrow.

437
00:19:02,609 --> 00:19:04,544
(Jeong Yoon steps away
to make room for Kang Hyeon.)

438
00:19:04,544 --> 00:19:06,746
He's got the wrong person.

439
00:19:06,746 --> 00:19:10,216
I think Ye Chan came
looking for Jeong Yoon.

440
00:19:12,885 --> 00:19:14,554
It's pretty romantic, isn't it?

441
00:19:14,554 --> 00:19:16,689
It's nice. No, it's more than nice.

442
00:19:18,258 --> 00:19:19,792
What's your type?

443
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:22,095
No.

444
00:19:22,996 --> 00:19:24,063
Straight to types.

445
00:19:24,063 --> 00:19:26,266
Hey, wait a little.

446
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:29,068
What's your type?

447
00:19:29,068 --> 00:19:30,270
My type...

448
00:19:30,970 --> 00:19:33,439
I think I'm drawn to feminine women.

449
00:19:33,439 --> 00:19:34,807
Feminine women.

450
00:19:34,807 --> 00:19:37,277
Someone with a mature feel.

451
00:19:37,277 --> 00:19:39,212
Someone who feels mature.

452
00:19:39,212 --> 00:19:40,280
That's very abstract.

453
00:19:40,513 --> 00:19:43,216
(Well...)

454
00:19:43,216 --> 00:19:45,551
Someone who, at first glance,

455
00:19:45,551 --> 00:19:48,688
feels chic or sophisticated.

456
00:19:48,688 --> 00:19:50,456
That's the kind of woman I prefer.

457
00:19:50,456 --> 00:19:52,792
Rather than someone
who's really cute and...

458
00:19:52,792 --> 00:19:54,861
- Bubbly?
- Yes, rather than that type.

459
00:19:54,861 --> 00:19:55,762
Really?

460
00:19:55,762 --> 00:19:57,430
I'm as bubbly as they come. This is bad.

461
00:19:57,430 --> 00:20:00,800
No, I mean,
I wouldn't call you bubbly, Kang Hyeon.

462
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:02,001
My goodness.

463
00:20:03,403 --> 00:20:05,071
Don't do that.

464
00:20:05,071 --> 00:20:07,340
Why would you say that?

465
00:20:07,774 --> 00:20:09,142
Ye Chan...

466
00:20:09,475 --> 00:20:11,711
doesn't even know
whether Kang Hyeon is bubbly.

467
00:20:11,711 --> 00:20:12,946
Right.

468
00:20:12,946 --> 00:20:16,749
He was just answering honestly
because she asked about his type.

469
00:20:16,749 --> 00:20:18,551
Rather than bubbly,

470
00:20:18,551 --> 00:20:20,620
this is just my personal guess,

471
00:20:20,620 --> 00:20:25,391
but at first,
when we were all still awkward and quiet,

472
00:20:25,391 --> 00:20:29,896
I think you made an effort
to be more cheerful.

473
00:20:29,896 --> 00:20:32,932
I'm curious who you are
once you let your guard down.

474
00:20:33,866 --> 00:20:35,735
You're really good at reading people.

475
00:20:36,336 --> 00:20:37,470
Should I become a fortune-teller?

476
00:20:38,771 --> 00:20:40,873
Right, I think that's
what feels considerate to me.

477
00:20:40,873 --> 00:20:43,543
So once the awkwardness fades,

478
00:20:43,543 --> 00:20:47,013
I thought I'd like to talk
more comfortably.

479
00:20:47,013 --> 00:20:48,014
Really?

480
00:20:48,448 --> 00:20:49,515
I see.

481
00:20:51,251 --> 00:20:53,186
Well, we can just get to know each other.

482
00:20:53,186 --> 00:20:55,722
We should. All of us.

483
00:20:55,722 --> 00:20:58,625
How many people
do you want to get to know more?

484
00:20:59,492 --> 00:21:01,160
For me, I've actually narrowed it down.

485
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:01,961
Don't say that.

486
00:21:01,961 --> 00:21:04,764
If you ask a question,
wait for the answer.

487
00:21:05,598 --> 00:21:06,799
After you ask a question,

488
00:21:06,799 --> 00:21:09,702
why answer it yourself first?

489
00:21:10,536 --> 00:21:11,638
Narrowed...

490
00:21:11,638 --> 00:21:13,139
She's way too impatient right now.

491
00:21:13,139 --> 00:21:15,541
She's staring so intently as she says,
"I've narrowed it down."

492
00:21:15,909 --> 00:21:16,910
"I've narrowed it down."

493
00:21:18,144 --> 00:21:19,779
For me, I've actually narrowed it down.

494
00:21:19,779 --> 00:21:21,614
Really? Already?

495
00:21:23,883 --> 00:21:25,952
I'm still deciding.
How many is it for you?

496
00:21:25,952 --> 00:21:27,253
Two.

497
00:21:27,253 --> 00:21:28,554
- Already?
- Yes.

498
00:21:28,955 --> 00:21:30,390
Two people.

499
00:21:30,390 --> 00:21:33,793
Do you mean people
you have romantic interest in?

500
00:21:36,129 --> 00:21:38,197
I'll be really honest.

501
00:21:38,197 --> 00:21:41,701
Surely she's not about to say,
"You're one of the two," right?

502
00:21:41,968 --> 00:21:43,636
For me, it's Seong Mo...

503
00:21:43,636 --> 00:21:45,705
and you, Ye Chan.

504
00:21:49,609 --> 00:21:51,544
- That's the first day, right?
- Don't say that.

505
00:21:51,544 --> 00:21:52,979
That's the first night, right?

506
00:21:54,547 --> 00:21:55,815
Well...

507
00:21:55,815 --> 00:21:59,586
Did you talk about things
like that with your mother?

508
00:22:00,186 --> 00:22:01,154
She picked you too, Ye Chan.

509
00:22:02,222 --> 00:22:03,122
She picked you too, Ye Chan.

510
00:22:04,224 --> 00:22:05,158
Seriously.

511
00:22:05,158 --> 00:22:06,526
Don't do that.

512
00:22:07,727 --> 00:22:09,829
Both Mom and I picked you, Ye Chan.

513
00:22:11,431 --> 00:22:13,666
Ye Chan's frozen. What do we do?

514
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:15,335
I see. Thank you so much.

515
00:22:15,335 --> 00:22:17,136
I told you, Ye Chan.

516
00:22:17,503 --> 00:22:18,905
"Does he go to church?"

517
00:22:18,905 --> 00:22:21,007
"Then we'd be on the same wavelength."

518
00:22:21,007 --> 00:22:22,976
So is religion quite important to you?

519
00:22:22,976 --> 00:22:24,143
It is.

520
00:22:24,644 --> 00:22:27,380
Shared values, to me,
means sharing the same faith.

521
00:22:27,380 --> 00:22:28,581
Religion.

522
00:22:28,581 --> 00:22:30,583
That's why I chose you. And you?

523
00:22:32,018 --> 00:22:34,921
I do have a religion, but...

524
00:22:36,256 --> 00:22:37,624
How should I put this?

525
00:22:38,858 --> 00:22:42,061
But you don't have to talk about it
if it makes you uncomfortable.

526
00:22:43,863 --> 00:22:44,931
It's okay.

527
00:22:44,931 --> 00:22:45,798
(Gulp)

528
00:22:45,798 --> 00:22:47,100
- No, I mean...
- No.

529
00:22:47,100 --> 00:22:49,535
I think it could make
anyone uncomfortable.

530
00:22:49,535 --> 00:22:50,470
And...

531
00:22:51,237 --> 00:22:52,672
you know.

532
00:22:52,672 --> 00:22:53,640
Yes.

533
00:22:54,574 --> 00:22:56,876
That's important to me.

534
00:22:56,876 --> 00:22:58,878
Does your mother feel the same way?

535
00:22:58,878 --> 00:22:59,746
Of course.

536
00:23:02,081 --> 00:23:03,182
I see.

537
00:23:06,552 --> 00:23:09,222
It's not an easy topic.

538
00:23:10,723 --> 00:23:14,060
I can tell that she has
strong religious convictions.

539
00:23:14,060 --> 00:23:16,229
I really could tell.

540
00:23:17,230 --> 00:23:21,534
As for whether I felt
a deeper romantic attraction,

541
00:23:21,534 --> 00:23:22,702
honestly,

542
00:23:23,503 --> 00:23:25,672
I don't think there was a spark yet.

543
00:23:26,739 --> 00:23:30,043
I did think I'd like to talk more
with you, Jeong Yoon.

544
00:23:30,043 --> 00:23:31,144
That's what I thought.

545
00:23:31,477 --> 00:23:34,714
I'm still thinking it over.

546
00:23:34,714 --> 00:23:35,848
Hobbies.

547
00:23:35,848 --> 00:23:38,551
Usually, I play with my dog at home.

548
00:23:40,753 --> 00:23:41,521
Things like that.

549
00:23:41,521 --> 00:23:43,856
- Or traveling. That's about it.
- Traveling?

550
00:23:43,856 --> 00:23:45,391
Do you travel around Korea and abroad?

551
00:23:45,391 --> 00:23:47,193
I like Southeast Asia.

552
00:23:47,193 --> 00:23:49,128
Southeast Asia is my favorite too.

553
00:23:49,128 --> 00:23:51,931
It's comfortable, and the food is good.

554
00:23:51,931 --> 00:23:53,900
Can you handle cilantro
and other strong flavors?

555
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:56,169
- Me too.
- I can eat almost everything.

556
00:23:56,169 --> 00:23:57,036
Me too.

557
00:23:57,036 --> 00:24:00,173
I like organ meats too.

558
00:24:00,173 --> 00:24:01,040
Me too.

559
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:03,610
Like tripe and intestines.

560
00:24:03,610 --> 00:24:06,613
That's unexpected for the image you give.

561
00:24:06,613 --> 00:24:08,414
Really? I'm a total Korean-food person.

562
00:24:08,414 --> 00:24:09,649
I'm a Korean-food person too.

563
00:24:09,649 --> 00:24:11,517
Korean food tastes best to me.

564
00:24:11,517 --> 00:24:12,318
Same.

565
00:24:12,318 --> 00:24:14,220
His reactions are completely different.

566
00:24:14,220 --> 00:24:17,557
When he talked to Kang Hyeon earlier,

567
00:24:18,024 --> 00:24:19,158
he only answered.

568
00:24:19,826 --> 00:24:21,661
- He couldn't even fully respond.
- Right.

569
00:24:21,661 --> 00:24:26,866
Because Kang Hyeon answered
her own questions.

570
00:24:26,866 --> 00:24:28,234
But now,

571
00:24:28,234 --> 00:24:29,936
he keeps asking questions.

572
00:24:29,936 --> 00:24:31,571
Right, they've got a good
back-and-forth going.

573
00:24:31,571 --> 00:24:34,107
People ask questions
when they want to know more.

574
00:24:34,874 --> 00:24:38,378
Then what's your type?

575
00:24:38,378 --> 00:24:40,013
For example, I like someone...

576
00:24:41,447 --> 00:24:44,918
whose job is in a field
I don't know much about.

577
00:24:46,185 --> 00:24:48,321
I do something genuinely interesting.

578
00:24:49,155 --> 00:24:51,658
- I'm curious.
- Really? I'm curious.

579
00:24:54,594 --> 00:24:55,695
Why?

580
00:24:55,695 --> 00:24:57,363
Right now,

581
00:24:57,363 --> 00:24:59,265
I personally find you...

582
00:25:00,733 --> 00:25:03,870
particularly intriguing.

583
00:25:03,870 --> 00:25:04,871
So...

584
00:25:04,871 --> 00:25:08,508
I suddenly felt like I'd like us...

585
00:25:08,508 --> 00:25:09,342
to have lots of fun conversations.

586
00:25:09,342 --> 00:25:11,444
I'm curious about lots of things too.

587
00:25:11,444 --> 00:25:16,583
Beyond first impressions,
I wanted to talk to you.

588
00:25:16,583 --> 00:25:19,886
Because there were things I wanted to ask.

589
00:25:19,886 --> 00:25:20,887
Really?

590
00:25:22,188 --> 00:25:23,756
This is going to send
his interest soaring.

591
00:25:23,756 --> 00:25:24,591
Exactly.

592
00:25:25,258 --> 00:25:28,728
I talked with Jeong Yoon
for about 30 minutes,

593
00:25:28,728 --> 00:25:31,397
and I started to get...

594
00:25:31,397 --> 00:25:32,665
a warm, fuzzy feeling.

595
00:25:33,967 --> 00:25:35,969
First, appearance-wise,

596
00:25:35,969 --> 00:25:39,172
she matched my type in the most ways.

597
00:25:39,172 --> 00:25:42,408
She also seems easygoing,

598
00:25:42,408 --> 00:25:46,312
and nothing made me lose interest.

599
00:25:47,180 --> 00:25:48,414
You look at their appearance first,

600
00:25:48,414 --> 00:25:51,384
then when you think,
"We have a lot in common,"

601
00:25:51,384 --> 00:25:52,452
that's when you fall in love.

602
00:25:52,452 --> 00:25:54,287
- Right.
- I see.

603
00:25:54,487 --> 00:25:57,790
Ye Chan says he's very curious about me.

604
00:25:57,790 --> 00:25:59,626
He says he has so many questions about me.

605
00:25:59,626 --> 00:26:05,565
He likes someone who works in a field...

606
00:26:05,565 --> 00:26:07,400
he knows nothing about,

607
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:09,202
someone who's good at leading their work.

608
00:26:10,370 --> 00:26:11,638
That's totally me.

609
00:26:12,839 --> 00:26:14,741
Her mother looks really tired.

610
00:26:16,009 --> 00:26:17,510
But she keeps asking her questions.

611
00:26:17,510 --> 00:26:18,578
She looks really tired.

612
00:26:19,579 --> 00:26:20,747
(Meanwhile,
Seong Mo is engrossed in a book.)

613
00:26:20,747 --> 00:26:23,182
He's suddenly reading a book.

614
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:26,686
"People only change..."

615
00:26:26,686 --> 00:26:28,821
"when they do one thing."

616
00:26:28,821 --> 00:26:29,956
"Move."

617
00:26:31,758 --> 00:26:33,459
Hey, even this says to move.

618
00:26:34,827 --> 00:26:36,029
But I'm tired.

619
00:26:37,230 --> 00:26:39,098
(Yawn)

620
00:26:39,098 --> 00:26:40,199
I'll move tomorrow.

621
00:26:42,302 --> 00:26:45,838
Our cast is pretty entertaining.

622
00:26:46,839 --> 00:26:47,707
(Meanwhile, the other contestant
keeps moving to find love.)

623
00:26:47,707 --> 00:26:50,410
This one seems steady and diligent.

624
00:26:50,410 --> 00:26:51,711
Where is he going?

625
00:26:54,581 --> 00:26:55,448
Is she there?

626
00:27:01,955 --> 00:27:04,457
Da Hye, are you there?

627
00:27:05,258 --> 00:27:06,092
Yes.

628
00:27:06,092 --> 00:27:07,961
I came to see you for a moment.

629
00:27:11,364 --> 00:27:12,899
- It's cold out, right?
- It is.

630
00:27:12,899 --> 00:27:13,800
Right.

631
00:27:14,334 --> 00:27:16,436
- I wanted to talk for a bit.
- One moment, please.

632
00:27:17,237 --> 00:27:18,504
How was your day?

633
00:27:19,205 --> 00:27:21,841
Today? It was eventful.

634
00:27:23,443 --> 00:27:25,511
- Would you like a glass of water?
- Yes.

635
00:27:25,511 --> 00:27:27,247
The water dispenser is small and cute.

636
00:27:27,247 --> 00:27:28,381
It's really pretty.

637
00:27:29,482 --> 00:27:30,984
The ice comes out really well.

638
00:27:31,484 --> 00:27:32,585
We won't need to worry about ice.

639
00:27:32,585 --> 00:27:33,453
Right?

640
00:27:33,453 --> 00:27:37,223
(Da Hye fixes Shin Woo
a glass of ice water.)

641
00:27:38,458 --> 00:27:39,359
Shall we clink our glasses?

642
00:27:39,359 --> 00:27:42,095
(They clink glasses.)

643
00:27:45,765 --> 00:27:48,568
I naturally turn my head and take a sip
after clinking glasses.

644
00:27:48,568 --> 00:27:51,237
I know, right?
I love how much ice it makes.

645
00:27:53,973 --> 00:27:57,577
Of everything today,
when you showed up just now,

646
00:27:57,577 --> 00:27:59,212
that probably caught me most off guard.

647
00:27:59,212 --> 00:28:01,714
I thought I had everything
roughly figured out,

648
00:28:01,714 --> 00:28:05,685
but I didn't see that coming at all.

649
00:28:05,685 --> 00:28:08,154
That's why I just dropped by.

650
00:28:08,154 --> 00:28:10,056
- Thank you.
- I didn't even know you were around.

651
00:28:10,456 --> 00:28:12,258
That really took courage.

652
00:28:13,927 --> 00:28:15,995
You make me want to know more
about you, Da Hye.

653
00:28:15,995 --> 00:28:17,797
He's really brave.

654
00:28:17,797 --> 00:28:18,932
I couldn't do that.

655
00:28:19,933 --> 00:28:23,002
I believe in first impressions.

656
00:28:24,437 --> 00:28:25,171
That's interesting.

657
00:28:25,171 --> 00:28:26,239
How about you, Da Hye?

658
00:28:27,974 --> 00:28:30,176
I think it depends on the moment.

659
00:28:30,176 --> 00:28:31,044
Every time you see someone?

660
00:28:31,044 --> 00:28:31,878
I think so.

661
00:28:32,946 --> 00:28:36,316
Have you had a chance
to talk to the others, Shin Woo?

662
00:28:36,316 --> 00:28:39,986
You're the only one
I feel romantically drawn to, Da Hye.

663
00:28:40,620 --> 00:28:42,555
Really?

664
00:28:42,555 --> 00:28:43,389
Goodness.

665
00:28:43,389 --> 00:28:44,324
(Laughing)

666
00:28:44,324 --> 00:28:46,526
He's amazing.

667
00:28:46,526 --> 00:28:49,429
You can really be that honest.

668
00:28:49,429 --> 00:28:50,930
Am I allowed to say that?

669
00:28:50,930 --> 00:28:53,066
I think that's so cool.

670
00:28:53,066 --> 00:28:54,234
I really respect that.

671
00:28:54,234 --> 00:28:57,870
Still, I wanted to tell you sincerely.

672
00:28:57,870 --> 00:28:58,805
Sincerely,

673
00:28:58,805 --> 00:29:01,140
when I looked back on my feelings,

674
00:29:01,140 --> 00:29:03,443
you were the only person
I was drawn to, Da Hye.

675
00:29:03,443 --> 00:29:04,844
You wanted to tell me that?

676
00:29:04,844 --> 00:29:05,945
Yes, I wanted to tell you.

677
00:29:06,613 --> 00:29:07,780
He even has such a lovely way with words.

678
00:29:07,780 --> 00:29:10,783
That's why it feels so sincere.

679
00:29:10,783 --> 00:29:15,488
A tone that brings out...

680
00:29:15,488 --> 00:29:18,391
- his sincerity and purity.
- Exactly.

681
00:29:18,391 --> 00:29:23,296
The more I see Shin Woo,

682
00:29:23,296 --> 00:29:26,299
the more charming he becomes.

683
00:29:26,299 --> 00:29:27,533
He grows on you.

684
00:29:28,334 --> 00:29:31,771
Thinking of others first
comes naturally to him,

685
00:29:31,771 --> 00:29:37,377
and he knows how to express that
without being overwhelming.

686
00:29:37,377 --> 00:29:39,112
I really admire that.

687
00:29:40,613 --> 00:29:41,881
(Shin Woo grins
while choosing tomorrow's outfit.)

688
00:29:41,881 --> 00:29:44,784
My secret-weapon pink.

689
00:29:44,784 --> 00:29:46,653
Nothing.

690
00:29:47,754 --> 00:29:49,589
I should wear my secret-weapon pink.

691
00:29:49,589 --> 00:29:52,091
He's so pure.

692
00:29:52,625 --> 00:29:54,961
Should I get to know anyone else?

693
00:29:54,961 --> 00:29:56,729
(The fluttering first night
comes to an end.)

694
00:29:57,564 --> 00:29:58,331
(Morning of Day 2)

695
00:29:58,331 --> 00:30:00,266
The sky is so pretty.

696
00:30:00,266 --> 00:30:01,301
Morning of Day Two.

697
00:30:02,402 --> 00:30:05,972
(A morning that starts with a walk)

698
00:30:06,506 --> 00:30:09,409
(Seong Mo's morning run)

699
00:30:09,409 --> 00:30:11,844
Just relax your eyes.

700
00:30:11,844 --> 00:30:13,179
(Meanwhile, the mothers and daughters
are getting dolled up.)

701
00:30:13,179 --> 00:30:16,583
Make sure you put lipstick in your bag.

702
00:30:16,583 --> 00:30:17,817
And put your eyebrows on too.

703
00:30:18,251 --> 00:30:20,086
(A mother who takes
her daughter's beauty routine seriously)

704
00:30:20,453 --> 00:30:23,489
(Everyone is busy getting ready.)

705
00:30:23,823 --> 00:30:26,492
Today is self-introduction day.

706
00:30:28,194 --> 00:30:29,195
Here it comes.

707
00:30:29,195 --> 00:30:30,163
Finally.

708
00:30:30,163 --> 00:30:32,498
- Self-introductions.
- Finally.

709
00:30:32,498 --> 00:30:35,835
This, to me,

710
00:30:35,835 --> 00:30:37,837
is the most important point in our show.

711
00:30:37,837 --> 00:30:38,671
It's a turning point.

712
00:30:38,671 --> 00:30:40,473
Everything changes here.

713
00:30:40,473 --> 00:30:41,741
Exactly.

714
00:30:41,741 --> 00:30:43,276
This is where it really begins.

715
00:30:43,977 --> 00:30:45,478
I'm nervous.

716
00:30:45,478 --> 00:30:46,479
Are you nervous?

717
00:30:46,479 --> 00:30:48,481
Why? You're worried you might do it?

718
00:30:48,481 --> 00:30:51,117
The moms do the introductions.

719
00:30:51,117 --> 00:30:55,622
On Match to Marry,
mothers introduce their children.

720
00:30:55,622 --> 00:30:58,625
The mothers were more nervous
last season too.

721
00:30:58,625 --> 00:31:01,995
Because every word they say...

722
00:31:01,995 --> 00:31:04,697
can make or break things for their child.

723
00:31:04,697 --> 00:31:06,299
This is what matters most right now.

724
00:31:06,299 --> 00:31:08,301
This is probably where it all begins.

725
00:31:08,902 --> 00:31:12,305
(How will the mothers' introductions
change the game?)

726
00:31:12,305 --> 00:31:13,373
Hello.

727
00:31:13,373 --> 00:31:17,277
(They gather one by one
for the introductions.)

728
00:31:18,111 --> 00:31:19,746
(Bows)

729
00:31:20,046 --> 00:31:21,481
(Bows)

730
00:31:22,148 --> 00:31:23,850
They'd be terrified.

731
00:31:24,851 --> 00:31:26,019
I'm suddenly nervous.

732
00:31:26,586 --> 00:31:29,856
- But I'm the one talking.
- Then why am I the one nervous?

733
00:31:29,856 --> 00:31:34,027
Today, only the women will be introduced.

734
00:31:34,027 --> 00:31:35,628
(Groan)

735
00:31:37,497 --> 00:31:39,566
Do them all at once.

736
00:31:39,566 --> 00:31:40,266
Why are you doing this?

737
00:31:40,266 --> 00:31:42,035
I'm mad. I'm really mad.

738
00:31:42,035 --> 00:31:45,104
I want to know what the men do.

739
00:31:45,471 --> 00:31:46,372
You got this.

740
00:31:50,143 --> 00:31:52,579
We'll start with Ahn Do Yoon's mother.

741
00:31:53,012 --> 00:31:53,947
You got this.

742
00:31:53,947 --> 00:31:56,115
You got this.

743
00:31:56,115 --> 00:31:58,785
(The first introduction begins.)

744
00:32:04,557 --> 00:32:08,294
Hello, I'm Son Hyeon Mi, Do Yoon's mom.

745
00:32:08,294 --> 00:32:09,229
My daughter...

746
00:32:09,229 --> 00:32:13,066
was born in 1999 and is 28 this year.

747
00:32:13,399 --> 00:32:16,970
was born in 1999 and is 28 this year.

748
00:32:16,970 --> 00:32:18,204
She's the same age as me.

749
00:32:18,204 --> 00:32:19,372
I knew it.

750
00:32:20,039 --> 00:32:21,641
She's young.

751
00:32:22,175 --> 00:32:24,043
No wonder she seemed so young.

752
00:32:24,677 --> 00:32:26,646
In Kwon, she's too young.

753
00:32:26,646 --> 00:32:27,914
She says she's too young.

754
00:32:28,448 --> 00:32:31,818
She works in
Samsung Electronics' Foundry Division...

755
00:32:31,818 --> 00:32:35,521
and has five years' experience
in defect control.

756
00:32:38,191 --> 00:32:39,759
She's...

757
00:32:41,361 --> 00:32:43,463
Ever since she appeared
in the previous episode,

758
00:32:43,463 --> 00:32:45,765
we said her mother seemed
incredibly proud of her daughter.

759
00:32:45,765 --> 00:32:46,566
Right, we did.

760
00:32:46,566 --> 00:32:49,602
Now we see why.

761
00:32:49,602 --> 00:32:52,438
She must be popular at work too.

762
00:32:53,373 --> 00:32:55,742
(28-year-old employee
at Samsung Electronics)

763
00:32:55,742 --> 00:32:56,576
Amazing.

764
00:32:56,576 --> 00:32:57,477
That's impressive.

765
00:32:58,378 --> 00:33:01,748
She joined Samsung Electronics
at just 24...

766
00:33:01,748 --> 00:33:04,150
and has never taken a break...

767
00:33:04,150 --> 00:33:06,819
from work since then.

768
00:33:06,819 --> 00:33:10,690
She currently lives in Dongtan,
near her workplace.

769
00:33:10,690 --> 00:33:11,424
Dongtan.

770
00:33:11,424 --> 00:33:15,194
She has saved
and invested wisely on her own,

771
00:33:15,194 --> 00:33:19,065
and has fully prepared
her own wedding fund.

772
00:33:19,065 --> 00:33:19,899
Nice.

773
00:33:20,533 --> 00:33:23,970
She grew up loved
in a comfortable, close-knit family,

774
00:33:23,970 --> 00:33:26,873
and is a wonderful daughter
who was raised well.

775
00:33:26,873 --> 00:33:29,142
She also takes meticulous care of herself.

776
00:33:29,142 --> 00:33:31,711
As you can see, at 170 cm,

777
00:33:31,711 --> 00:33:35,982
she always stays between 48 and 49 kg.

778
00:33:35,982 --> 00:33:37,517
Always.

779
00:33:37,517 --> 00:33:39,252
She's tall too.

780
00:33:39,252 --> 00:33:40,853
Even revealing her weight.

781
00:33:40,853 --> 00:33:42,422
She's 170 cm tall.

782
00:33:42,422 --> 00:33:43,523
She really is something to be proud of.

783
00:33:44,324 --> 00:33:45,725
I'm jealous of her legs.

784
00:33:45,725 --> 00:33:46,659
(Proud mom mode on)

785
00:33:47,894 --> 00:33:49,662
Career-wise,

786
00:33:49,662 --> 00:33:52,098
rather than someone who runs a business,

787
00:33:52,098 --> 00:33:55,001
she prefers someone
who diligently works...

788
00:33:55,001 --> 00:33:57,303
a regular office job, like she does.

789
00:33:57,303 --> 00:33:58,638
An office worker.

790
00:33:58,638 --> 00:34:02,175
Even without side dishes, someone who can
enjoy rice with chili paste...

791
00:34:02,175 --> 00:34:05,011
and a fried egg on top...

792
00:34:05,011 --> 00:34:07,280
would be wonderful.

793
00:34:07,280 --> 00:34:08,915
That's all.

794
00:34:10,984 --> 00:34:12,352
Please feel free to ask questions.

795
00:34:12,352 --> 00:34:13,686
What if nobody asks?

796
00:34:14,621 --> 00:34:18,992
People tend to marry later
in the Seoul metro area these days.

797
00:34:18,992 --> 00:34:22,228
Were you thinking about marriage
at a fairly young age?

798
00:34:22,228 --> 00:34:24,364
I entered the workforce early,

799
00:34:24,364 --> 00:34:25,632
so I'm the youngest at work,

800
00:34:25,632 --> 00:34:28,167
and all my senior colleagues
are getting married.

801
00:34:28,167 --> 00:34:29,736
So I think that's what got me
thinking about it.

802
00:34:30,837 --> 00:34:33,406
How big an age gap is okay?

803
00:34:33,406 --> 00:34:34,774
As for an age gap,

804
00:34:34,774 --> 00:34:36,943
I've always liked older men,

805
00:34:36,943 --> 00:34:39,512
so if I met someone on a blind date,

806
00:34:39,512 --> 00:34:41,147
I think I've dated men
up to five or six years older.

